<float-pair|integer|string>
Interpolation options for the context function '{tkn}'

domain.{arg}=<float-pair>:
  Domain interval for the function argument '{arg}' where the interpolation needs to be made.

intervals=<integer>:
  Number of sub-divisions to split the interpolation scheme. Default: 1000

out_of_bounds=<string>
  Type of behavior when function is evaluated out of the defined domain bounds. Default: error
    Possible selections are:
      * error:    Throw an error when function '{tkn}' is evaluated outside of 'domain.{arg}'.
      * clamp:    Clamps the arguments of the function '{tkn}' to be evaluated inside of 'domain.{arg}'.
